UC-01: User Login

Primary Actor: Administrator / Hospital Staff / Authorized Staff / Donor

Preconditions

User is registered in the system

Valid login credentials are available

Main Flow

User enters username and password

System validates credentials

User is authenticated successfully

System redirects user to dashboard

Alternative Flow

2a. Invalid credentials entered

System displays error message

User is asked to retry

Postconditions

User is logged into the system

Access is granted based on role

UC-02: Register Blood Donor

Primary Actor: Administrator

Preconditions

Administrator is logged in

Main Flow

Administrator selects “Register Donor”

Enters donor personal and medical details

System validates entered data

Donor record is saved successfully

Alternative Flow

3a. Missing or invalid details

System displays validation error

Postconditions

New donor is registered in the system

UC-03: Update Donor Information

Primary Actor: Administrator / Authorized Staff

Preconditions

User is logged in

Donor record exists

Main Flow

User searches for donor

Selects donor record

Updates required details

System saves updated information

Alternative Flow

1a. Donor not found

System displays message

Postconditions

Donor details are updated

UC-04: Manage Blood Inventory

Primary Actor: Administrator / Authorized Staff

Preconditions

User is logged in

Main Flow

User selects inventory management option

Adds or updates blood unit details

System updates inventory records

Expiry dates are monitored

Alternative Flow

2a. Invalid quantity or data

System displays error

Postconditions

Blood inventory is updated accurately

UC-05: Search Blood Availability

Primary Actor: Hospital Staff

Preconditions

Hospital staff is logged in

Main Flow

Staff selects search option

Enters required blood group

System displays availability details

Alternative Flow

3a. Blood not available

System displays “Not Available” message

Postconditions

Blood availability information is shown

UC-06: Request Blood

Primary Actor: Hospital Staff

Preconditions

User is logged in

Blood availability is checked

Main Flow

Hospital staff submits blood request

Enters patient and blood details

System records request

Request status is set to “Pending”

Alternative Flow

2a. Invalid request details

System displays error

Postconditions

Blood request is successfully submitted

UC-07: Approve / Reject Blood Request

Primary Actor: Administrator

Preconditions

Administrator is logged in

Blood request exists

Main Flow

Admin views pending requests

Checks inventory availability

Approves or rejects request

System updates request status

Alternative Flow

2a. Insufficient blood stock

Request is rejected

Postconditions

Request status is updated

Inventory is adjusted if approved

UC-08: Send Notifications

Primary Actor: System / Administrator

Preconditions

Relevant event occurs (low stock, emergency, approval)

Main Flow

System detects triggering event

Notification message is generated

Message is sent to users/donors

Alternative Flow

3a. Notification failure

System logs error

Postconditions

Users are notified successfully

Conclusion

This use case documentation clearly defines system behavior through structured flows, ensuring clarity in functionality and serving as a strong foundation for design and testing.
